<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4832/41–42.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 94.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No 210 of the 29th ultimo, inclosing copy of the note by which you
                            expressed to the foreign office on the same day this Government’s
                            appreciation of Brazil’s good offices in taking charge of American
                            interests in Venezuela.</p>
                        <p>Your note is approved.</p>
                        <p>With renewed expressions of appreciation of Brazilian good offices and
                            good will,</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>